user
I've revised the implementation to address your round-0 findings:

1. Multi-row authoring: new POST /planner/{task_id}/add_row route + 'add another row' button on the form. Server-rendered re-render preserves user input. Tests in test_planner_flow.py::TestMultiRow cover the add-row flow, the skip-fully-blank-row submit path, and the all-blank rejection.

2. Retry-before-orphan now catches Exception (not just DispatchError) so transport-shaped failures from the wire client (httpx.HTTPError etc) are retried. Definitive store-domain errors (WrongToken/IllegalTransition/ConflictingResubmission/InvalidPrecondition) still short-circuit. Returns (ok, banner) so the orphan page can show the canonical error name. Test in test_planner_flow.py::TestRetryBeforeOrphan exercises a non-DispatchError transport failure -> 3 retries -> orphan with class name in banner.

3. Per-session claim isolation: _CLAIMS is now keyed by (session.csrf, task_id). Two browser sessions (even with the same configured worker_id) get different CSRF tokens at sign-in, so they cannot reuse each other's claims. Test in test_planner_flow.py::TestPerSessionClaimIsolation reproduces the cross-session draft-page request and asserts it redirects with claim+missing.

4. Stranded-claim e2e now spawns a third subprocess (the real orchestrator with no plan tasks) to prove that run_orchestrator_loop's per-iteration sweep_expired_claims call is what reclaims. The orchestrator quiesces after observing no progress; the test asserts task state and event log.

5. Orphan page renders the canonical eden://error/<name> banner from the retry's outcome.

Results: 444 unit tests + 3 e2e tests pass; ruff and pyright clean; markdownlint clean.

Please re-review against your round-0 findings — were each addressed? Any new issues?
