**Findings**
- Medium: the round-0 submit-recovery issue is still open. Definitive submit errors (`WrongToken`, `IllegalTransition`, `ConflictingResubmission`, `InvalidPrecondition`) now produce a canonical banner, but they still route to the orphan page via [_retry_submit()](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/planner.py:282) and [submit_plan()](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/planner.py:267) instead of re-rendering the planner flow with “claim again” and preserved input. That was the remaining plan mismatch from round 0, and there is still no test covering the promised submit-time recovery path for those definitive wire errors.

**Round-0 Status**
- Addressed: multi-row authoring is now real. The new [add_row route](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/planner.py:140), [button in the template](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/templates/planner_claim.html:55), and blank-row handling in [forms.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/forms.py:48) close the browser/UI gap. The new `TestMultiRow` coverage in [test_planner_flow.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_planner_flow.py:117) is the right shape.
- Addressed: retry-before-orphan now covers real transport-shaped failures from the wire client. `_retry_submit()` catches non-store exceptions and retries them in [planner.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/planner.py:282), which matches the `StoreClient` behavior in [client.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-wire/src/eden_wire/client.py:113). The new retry test in [test_planner_flow.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_planner_flow.py:242) covers that path.
- Addressed: per-session claim isolation is fixed. Claims are now keyed by `(session.csrf, task_id)` in [planner.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/planner.py:41), and the regression test in [test_planner_flow.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_planner_flow.py:213) closes the cross-session reuse hole.
- Addressed: the stranded-claim e2e now proves the operational path, not just the helper. [test_e2e_real_subprocess.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_e2e_real_subprocess.py:253) now spawns the real orchestrator, and [loop.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/orchestrator/src/eden_orchestrator/loop.py:68) is the path being exercised.
- Addressed: the orphan page now shows the canonical banner in [planner_orphaned.html](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/templates/planner_orphaned.html:5).

I reran `reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_planner_flow.py` and `reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_e2e_real_subprocess.py`; both passed locally.

Overall: 4 of the 5 round-0 findings are fixed. I would still require the definitive submit-error recovery flow to match the plan before calling this fully ready.
